-- U.S. RESEARCH ROUNDUP-Marvell, Qualcomm, TD Ameritrade
-- 
-- Wed Jun 11, 2014 01:52AM EDT
-- None



June 11 (Reuters) - Wall Street securities analysts revised their ratings and price targets on several U.S.-listed companies, including Marvell, Qualcomm and TD Ameritrade, on Wednesday.

HIGHLIGHTS * Arbor Realty Trust <ABR.N>: MLV Equity Research starts with buy * Marvell Technology Group <MRVL.O>: Nomura raises to buy from neutral * Qualcomm <QCOM.O>: Nomura raises price target to $90   Following is a summary of research actions on U.S. companies reported by Reuters on Wednesday. Stock entries are in alphabetical order.* Arbor Realty Trust <ABR.N>: MLV Equity Research starts with buy; price target $9 * Avanir Pharmaceuticals <AVNR.O>: Jefferies raises price target to $5 from $4; rating hold  * Canadian Pacific Railway <CP.N>: BMO raises price target to $215 from $205; outperform * Casey's General Stores <CASY.O>: Raymond James raises target to $80 from $77; outperform * Covanta Holding Corp <CVA.N>: Credit Suisse raises price target to $22 from $19; neutral * Ikang Healthcare Group <KANG.O>: Oppenheimer raises target to $19 from $16; outperform  * Kapstone Paper And Packaging <KS.N>: KeyBanc raises price target to $35 from $30; buy * Lpath <LPTN.O>: MLV Equity Research cuts price target to $11 from $13; rating buy  * Marvell Technology Group <MRVL.O>: Nomura raises to buy from neutral  * Micron Technology <MU.O>: Credit Suisse raises price target to $50 from $30; outperform  * Qualcomm <QCOM.O>: Nomura raises price target to $90; rating buy * TD Ameritrade <AMTD.N>: Credit Suisse cuts price target to $33 from $35; rating neutral